		<div class="apptitle">HOW AND WHERE CAN YOU APPLY YOUR SKILLS?</div>
		<div class="appsub">There are several ways to apply your technology skills outside of work and school. You can contribute to open-source projects, where developers worldwide collaborate on 
		publicly available software projects to gain experience, learn new skills, and build a website. Freelancing offers another opportunity to work on short-term projects for clients on a contract
		basis, such as web and mobile app development or digital marketing.<br /><br />You can also volunteer your technology skills for non-profit organizations, using them to help build websites, create social
		media campaigns, and manage data. Finally, starting your own technology-related project is an option, allowing you to work on something you're passionate about and set your own goals while 
		building your portfolio.</div> 
	</div>
		
			<div class="appcareers-text-container">
